You have a choice as a business owner to show solidarity with political ideologies and losing business or just shutting up. Simply put blue lives do not exist it's a career path and a reactionary movement.

That can be a great thing! I personally have had good experiences but even if I had a bad one it's not worth it to publicly shame someone over a drink. You don't know what's going on in their life. I only return here because my children seems to like it here so much. I didn't even ask for the employee's name because I have no doubt she would have given me a fake one. After the second attempt at my drink (a hot latte with a SF flavor) was still wrong, along with the worst attitude from the employee, I asked for a refund since my order was causing so much trouble. She simply huffed that she couldn't give me a refund and would "have to remake my order." Don't waste your time here.

I used to love this place. My friends and I went here all the time in high school, then we continued to return when we visited home during college breaks. The drink quality, the atmosphere, the friendly staff all made the place feel happy, safe, and cozy. However, I was very disappointed to see this establishment display a blue lives matter flag on their property, and am so sad to no longer be able to support personally or recommend their business to others as I have done for years. I understand they were honoring a fallen officer with a drink and scholarship donation, however this flag has been associated with so much hate and it is unnecessary to add the flag to what could have been a beautiful gesture in someone's memory.

French Express Coffee is HANDS DOWN the best coffee house in town!
They are the friendliest bunch , I consider them extended family at this point! The coffee? It is roasted to perfection. Bring your dog in, talk with a friend on the couch, draw on the wall, is a gigantic chalkboard. Or, sit outside and munch on fresh,YUMMY baked goods. All the while savoring each sip of a lovely robust coffee. Did I forget to mention the selection of chai teas, green teas, healthy smoothies? I cannot recall all of the drinks. Not so many that it's impossible to choose and I like this fact!
I have yet to find anything that comes close to matching FRENCH COFFEE EXPRESS and I am not referring to proximity!!
Since I brought up proximity I ll add in "I feel lucky to have another FRENCH EXPRESS COFFEE HOUSE in China Groove.
My personal favorite part about this communal establishment!!?Hard to choose yet from a business stance?Consistency is   ! All employees work both stores( most employees) so the consistency which is one of the three most important ingredients in the food industry, is stellar! Number one? Consistency, my friends and the second? And boy are they consistent! Every,single,coffee I have had from French Express is like the one before, just the way I like it! Word of mouth is KEY, everyone talks about Coffee Express for due reason;) Third? Staff! One must visit, relax, and enjoy a coffee to realize that simply stopping by FRENCH EXPRESS COFFEE, to say hi? Is worth part of anyones day! Oh- or you can use to drive thru! Enjoy your coffee!
Have a grateful day!!

Ever since then me and my old man try to stop by at least once a week after my treatment to get coffee in the morning. The staff and people that work the drive thru have been absolutely amazing. It's never expensive and they are always, ALWAYS friendly. It's something I can look forward to to keep me going. I got my standard red eye with cream.  The barista was pleasant, greeted me with a smile, and knew what I was ordering.  (You would be surprised the number if people who don't know what a red eye is.). She was fast, accurate, and the transaction was just what you would hope for in your first caffeine of the day.  And my order was perfect. Perfect temperature, just the right amount of kick from the shot, and balanced smoothly with a splash of cream.  This place is well worth a visit.
